  <body>
    <div class="container page" style="background-image: url(<%= Rails.root.to_s %>/app/assets/images/annual_report_bg.png); height: 1460px;">
      <div style="position: absolute; top: 30px; left: 100px; width: 700px;">
        <p style="color: white; font-size: 70px;"><b><%= @annual_report.exam_start.year %></b></p>
        <p style="color: #FFCD00; font-size: 40px; margin-top: -60px;"><b><%= @business.business_name %></b></p>
      </div>
      <div style="float: left; top:420px;" class="circles"></div><div class="circles2" style="top:420px;"></div>
      <h1 style="font-size: 130px; text-align: center; letter-spacing: 10px; position: relative; z-index: 3; top: -150px; font-weight: bold;"><b>ANNUAL CPR REPORT</b></h1>
      <p style="color: #FFCD00; font-size: 44px; text-align: right; font-weight: bold; letter-spacing: 2px; position: relative; right: 100px; top:100px;">PREPARED BY:</p>
      <p style="color: white; font-size: 26px; text-align: right; position: relative; right: 100px; top:100px; margin-top: -40px; font-weight: bold;"><%= @business.business_name %></p>
    </div>
    <div class="container page" style="background-image: url(<%= Rails.root.to_s %>/app/assets/images/annual_report_bg2.png); background-size: 100%; background-clip: content-box; height: 1460px;">
      <p style="font-size: 60px; display: table-caption; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 4px; padding-left: 100px; padding-top:100px; margin-bottom: -20px; font-weight: 900;"><b>COMPLIANCE PROGRAM REVIEW</b></p>
      <div style="width: 330px; height: 330px; position: relative; left: 600px; top: -120px; border-radius: 50%; background:black; ">
        <p style="color: #FFCD00; font-size: 64px; text-align: center; padding-top: 25%; padding-bottom: -30px; font-family: Canela;">12</p>
        <p style="color: #FFFFFF; font-size: 20px; ; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; max-width: 240px; margin: auto; margin-top:-50px; line-height: 1.5;">core areas of the compliance program was reviewed</p>
      </div>
      <div style="width: 530px; height: 530px; background-color: #FFCD00; z-index: 3; position: absolute; left: -40px; bottom: 500px !important;" class="circles">
        <p style="font-size: 106px; font-weight: bold; letter-spacing: 10px; margin-bottom: -20px; text-align: center; padding-top:40px; font-family: Canela;"><%= @annual_report.findings_report[:percentage] %>%</p>
        <p style="font-size: 24px; text-align: center; line-height: 1.5; padding-top: 10px; padding-left: 60px; width: 400px;">of the areas reviewed did not have any notable findings or recommendations for improvement</p>
      </div>
      <p style="padding-left: 70px; font-size: 20px; max-width: 560px; line-height: 1.5; position: relative; bottom: -300px;"><%= @business.business_name %> (or the "Company") conducted an annual review of its compliance program from <%= @annual_report.created_at.strftime("%Y %B %d") %> through <%= @annual_report.updated_at.strftime("%Y %B %d") %>. This report contains specific observations and recommendations concerning the Company’s practices, including general context and references to applicable securities laws.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="container page">
      <h1 style="text-align: center; font-size: 48px; letter-spacing: 5px; padding: 30px 0px; padding-top: 130px;">REPORT CONTENTS</h1>
      <table style="border: 1px solid white; font-weight: 700; border-spacing: 0 -300px; margin: 0 auto; width: 820px;">
        <tr><td style="border: 1px solid white;"><span class="yellow";>01</span></td><td style="border: 1px solid white;"><p style="letter-spacing: 2px; font-size: 30px; margin-bottom: 10px;"><b>EXECUTIVE SUMMARY</b><br></p><p style="font-size: 20px;">Summary of the Annual Compliance Program Review process and results</p></td></tr>
        <tr><td style="border: 1px solid white;"><span class="yellow">02</span></td><td style="border: 1px solid white;"><p style="letter-spacing: 2px; font-size: 30px; margin-bottom: 10px;"><b>MATERIAL BUSINESS CHANGES</b><br></p><p style="font-size: 20px;">Overview of pertinent changes within the business that occurred since the last review</p></td></tr>
        <tr><td style="border: 1px solid white;"><span class="yellow">03</span></td><td style="border: 1px solid white;"><p style="letter-spacing: 2px; font-size: 30px; margin-bottom: 10px;"><b>MATERIAL REGULATORY CHANGES</b><br></p><p style="font-size: 20px;">Overview of pertinent regulatory changes that effected the business since the last review and how we addressed those changes at the time</p></td></tr>
        <tr><td style="border: 1px solid white;"><span class="yellow">04</span></td><td style="border: 1px solid white;"><p style="letter-spacing: 2px; font-size: 30px; margin-bottom: 10px;"><b>FINDINGS & RECOMMENDATIONS</b><br></p><p style="font-size: 20px;">Itemization of the findings from this review and our recommended corrective actions</p></td></tr>
        <tr><td style="border: 1px solid white;"><span class="yellow">05</span></td><td style="border: 1px solid white;"><p style="letter-spacing: 2px; font-size: 30px; margin-bottom: 10px;"><b>CONCLUSION</b><br></p><p style="font-size: 20px;">Summary of our perspective on this review and its purpose and limitations</p></td></tr>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="container page texty">
      <div style="background-image: url(<%= Rails.root.to_s %>/app/assets/images/annual_report_bg3.png); background-size: 100%; background-clip: content-box; height: 230px;">
       <h1 style="padding: 100px 0px; font-size: 38px; text-align: center; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: 5px; color: white;"><b>EXECUTIVE SUMMARY</b></h1> 
      </div>
      <p style="padding-top: 20px;"><%= @business.business_name %> reviewed certain books and records covering the time period from <%= @annual_report.review_start.strftime("%Y %B %d") %> through <%= @annual_report.review_end.strftime("%Y %B %d") %> (the "Review Period"). This comprehensive review of our compliance program was designed to assess our compliance with the following:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Securities regulations;</li>
        <li>Internal policies and procedures;</li>
        <li>Industry best practices; and</li>
        <li>Knowledge of regulatory expectations.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To ensure we execute on our fiduciary duty to our clients throughout each facet of our business practice, <%= @business.business_name %> broke down the review of our compliance program into twelve core areas we deemed material to every advisory firm’s operations. These topics also encompass the risk areas highlighted by the Securities Exchange Commission (“SEC”) in their adopting release for Rule 206(4)-7 (the “Compliance Program Rule”), which provided guidance to federally registered investment advisers on the areas, at a minimum, their policies and procedures are expected to address. We assessed the adequacy and effectiveness of our policies and procedures in these areas and sample tested relevant documentation demonstrating compliance with our policies and applicable securities laws. <br>The twelve core areas we reviewed were:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Proprietary trading of the Company and personal trading activities of its access persons;</li>
        <li>Privacy safeguards like identity theft prevention and cybersecurity controls for the protection of sensitive client records and information, as well as, the Company’s proprietary information;</li>
        <li>Portfolio management processes like consistency of portfolios with clients' investment objectives, allocation of investment opportunities among clients, and applicable regulatory restrictions;</li>
        <li>Trading practices, including procedures by which the Company satisfies its best execution obligation, uses client brokerage to obtain research and other services ("soft dollar arrangements"), and allocates aggregated trades among clients, when applicable;</li>
        <li>Processes to value client holdings;</li>
        <li>Proxy voting practices;</li>
        <li>The timely and accurate filing and distribution of regulatory disclosures made to clients and regulators;</li>
        <li>Marketing advisory services, including the use of solicitors;</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="container page texty" style="padding-top: 50px;">
      <ul>
        <li>Safeguarding of client assets from conversion or inappropriate use by employees;</li>
        <li>The accurate creation of required records and their maintenance in a manner that secures them from unauthorized alteration or use and protects them from untimely destruction;</li>
        <li>Business continuity plans; and</li>
        <li>The establishment, maintenance and general execution of this compliance program based upon the Company’s specific operational and business practice risks.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>While the review addressed each of the areas noted above, <%= @business.business_name %> prioritized areas we believed to present the most risk to the Company and/or our clients.</p>
      <% if @annual_report.annual_review_employees.where.not(name: nil).where.not(name: "").present? %>
        <p>To ensure that the policies and procedures that establish the backbone of our compliance program were reflective our our business practices, we interviewed the following employees to gain additional perspective into the Company’s operations and how our employees, in their own words, executed their day to day duties:</p>
        <ul>
          <% @annual_report.annual_review_employees.where.not(name: nil).where.not(name: "").each do |emp| %>
            <li><%= emp.name %>, <%= emp.title %>, <%= emp.department %></li>
          <% end %>
        </ul>
      <% end %>
      <p>Based on <%= @business.business_name %>’s review, the Company’s compliance program appears <%= ["poorly tailored", "reasonably tailored", "well-tailored"][@annual_report.tailored_lvl-1] %> relative to the scope and nature of the Company’s operations.</p>
      <p><%= @annual_report.comments %></p>
    </div>
    <div class="container page texty">
      <div style="background-image: url(<%= Rails.root.to_s %>/app/assets/images/annual_report_bg3.png); background-size: 100%; background-clip: content-box; height: 230px;">
       <h1 style="padding: 100px 0px; font-size: 38px; text-align: center; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 5px; color: white;">MATERIAL BUSINESS CHANGES</h1> 
      </div>
      <p style="padding-top:20px;">Changes in the Company’s business practices may have an impact on the policies and procedures that we have established. Therefore, the Company has identified any material business changes that occurred during the Review Period and to give special consideration to whether we have properly amended our compliance policies and procedures to address any operational and compliance risks that may have arisen out of these changes.</p>
      <% if @annual_report.business_changes.where.not(change: nil).where.not(change: "").present? %>
        <p>The following material business changes occurred during the Review Period:</p>
        <ul>
          <% @annual_report.business_changes.where.not(change: nil).where.not(change: "").each do |change| %>
            <li><%= change.change %></li>
          <% end %>
        </ul>
      <% else %>
        <p>There were no material business changes that occurred during the Review Period.</p>
      <% end %>
    </div>
    <div class="container page texty">
      <div style="background-image: url(<%= Rails.root.to_s %>/app/assets/images/annual_report_bg3.png); background-size: 100%; background-clip: content-box; height: 230px;">
       <h1 style="padding: 100px 0px; font-size: 38px; text-align: center; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 5px; color: white;">MATERIAL REGULATORY CHANGES</h1> 
      </div>
      <p style="padding-top:20px;">The regulatory landscape is constantly changing to address the ever-evolving risks of the financial industry. <%= @business.business_name %> endeavors to stay apprised of its regulatory obligations and properly address new requirements by making changes to our policies and procedures, as appropriate. </p>
      <% if @annual_report.regulatory_changes.where.not(change: nil).where.not(change: "").present? %>
        <p>The following are the material regulatory changes we identified during the Review Period and the Company’s response to these changes:</p>
        <ul>
          <% @annual_report.regulatory_changes.where.not(change: nil).where.not(change: "").each do |change| %>
            <li><%= change.change %> – <%= change.response %></li>
          <% end %>
        </ul>
      <% else %>
        <p>There were no material regulatory changes identified during the Review Period.</p>
      <% end %>
    </div>
    <div class="container page texty">
      <div style="background-image: url(<%= Rails.root.to_s %>/app/assets/images/annual_report_bg3.png); background-size: 100%; background-clip: content-box; height: 230px;">
       <h1 style="padding: 100px 0px; font-size: 38px; text-align: center; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 5px; color: white;">FINDINGS & RECOMMENDATIONS</h1> 
      </div>
      <p style="padding-top:20px;">As we reviewed each of the twelve core areas of our advisory business, <%= @business.business_name %> notated issues that required corrective action, as well as, general items that we felt had room for improvement.</p>
      <p>Thus, these findings and recommendations are presented in three parts:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Identification of an any perceived weaknesses or compliance issues at the Company;</li>
        <li>The recommendation for how the Company  may address the findings noted; and</li>
        <li>An assigned risk level of low, moderate, or high to the perceived regulatory enforcement action risk the finding presents to the business</li>
      </ul>
      <p><p>This risk rating is purely subjective and is not reflective of any rating or ranking system adopted by or approved by a regulator, rating agency, or other third party. The risk ratings can be understood as follows:</p>  
      <ul style="page-break-inside: avoid;">
        <li>
          <span style="color: #00a746; font-weight: bold;">LOW</span> – Reflects a minor technical rule violation or recommended enhancement based on best business practices. These findings may or may not appear within a deficiency letter during the course of a regulatory examination.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span style="color: #ffb800; font-weight: bold;">MODERATE</span> – Reflects an area of concern that could attract more regulatory scrutiny. These findings are most likely to be commented on within a deficiency letter during the course of a regulatory examination.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span style="color: #ff0000; font-weight: bold;">HIGH</span> – Reflects a finding of the highest level of concern and requiring immediate attention from the Company. These findings will be heavily scrutinized and may give rise to a potential enforcement action without proper additional review and remediation during the course of a regulatory examination.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <% ComplianceCategory.all.each_with_index do |compliance_category,cc_i| %>
      <div class="container page texty">
        <table align="center" style="border: 1px solid white; font-weight: 700; border-spacing: 0 -300px; margin: 0 auto; width: 820px;">
          <tr><td style="border: 1px solid white;"><span class="black"><%= (cc_i+1).to_s.rjust(2, "0") %></span></td><td style="border: 1px solid white;"><p style="font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: 2px; font-size: 32px; margin-bottom: -10px; position: absolute; left: 330px; top: 65px;"><%= compliance_category.name.upcase %></p></td></tr>
        </table>
        <% unfailed_topics = @annual_report.findings_report[:unfailed_topics][compliance_category.id] %>
        <% if unfailed_topics.nil? %>
          <p><%= raw(compliance_category.findings_everywhere.split("\n").map(&Proc.new { |n| n[0..2] == " - " ? "<span class='bulletpoint'></span>#{n[2..n.length]}" : n }).join("<br>").gsub("[business_name]", @business.business_name)) %></p>
        <% else %>
          <p><%= raw(compliance_category.description.split("\n").map(&Proc.new { |n| n[0..2] == " - " ? "<span class='bulletpoint'></span>#{n[2..n.length]}" : n }).join("<br>").gsub("[business_name]", @business.business_name)) %></p>
          <ul>
            <% unfailed_topics.each do |line| %>
              <li><%= line %></li>
            <% end %>
          </ul>
        <% end %>
        <% this_findings = @annual_report.findings.where(compliance_category: compliance_category.id).where.not(finding: "") %>
        <% if this_findings.any? %>
          <% if !unfailed_topics.nil? %>
            <p><%= raw(compliance_category.however.split("\n").map(&Proc.new { |n| n[0..2] == " - " ? "<span class='bulletpoint'></span>#{n[2..n.length]}" : n }).join("<br>").gsub("[business_name]", @business.business_name)) %></p>
          <% end %>
          <table style="width: 90%; margin: 0 auto; margin-top: 50px;">
            <tr><td style="text-align: center; border: 2px solid white; border-left: 2px solid black; border-bottom: 2px solid black; background: #000000; color: #FFFFFF;"><p style="font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700;">Finding</p></td><td style="text-align: center; border: 2px solid white; background: #000000; color: #FFFFFF; border-left: 2px solid black; border-bottom: 2px solid black;"><p style="font-weight: 700; font-size: 20px;">Recommendation</p></td><td style="text-align: center; border: 2px solid white; background: #000000; color: #FFFFFF; border-bottom: 2px solid black; border-right: 2px solid black;"><p style="font-weight: 700; font-size: 20px;">Risk</p></td></tr>
            <% this_findings.each do |finding| %>
              <tr>
                <td style="padding-left: 10px; border: 2px solid black; font-size: 20px;"><%= finding.finding %></td>
                <td style="padding-left: 10px; border: 2px solid black; font-size: 20px;"><%= finding.action %></td>
                <td style="font-weight: 900; text-align: center; border: 2px solid black; font-size: 20px; background-color: <%= risk_colors[finding.risk_lvl-1] %>"><%= risk_captions[finding.risk_lvl-1] %></td>
              </tr>
            <% end %>
          </table>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    <% end %>

    <div class="container page texty">
      <div style="background-image: url(<%= Rails.root.to_s %>/app/assets/images/annual_report_bg3.png); background-size: 100%; background-clip: content-box; height: 230px;">
       <h1 style="padding: 100px 0px; font-size: 38px; text-align: center; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 5px; color: white;">CONCLUSION</h1> 
      </div>
      <p style="padding-top:20px;"><%= @business.business_name %> made efforts to assess our compliance program based upon the review of our books and records along with the oral representations from our employees. Where practicable, we conducted testing of our documentation on a sample basis. Our findings and recommendations reflect our understanding of applicable regulations, compliance requirements, and business risks posed by our current operations only as of the time of the review.</p>
      <p>Annual compliance program reviews like this assist us in detecting not only deficiencies in our program, but also where there may be room for improvement. Therefore, the lack of or presence of findings and recommendations herein is not a direct reflection of <%= @business.business_name %>’s compliance with regulatory laws. It is our goal to find ways to enhance our compliance program, and thus, our business practices.</p>
      <p>This report is intended solely for the information and use of <%= @business.business_name %>.</p>
    </div>  
  </body>